{"title":"DT Swiss expands Ratchet LN upgrade to road bikes, adds faster 36T MTB kit option","link":"https://bikerumor.com/dt-swiss-expands-ratchet-ln-upgrade-to-road-bikes-adds-faster-36t-mtb-kit-option/","date":1639745931000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"DT Swiss Ratchet LN Upgrade Kit Road\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074927/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_angled.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-281079\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>DT Swiss brings their Ratchet LN DIY upgrade kits to more riders with new road-specific options. Just like on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dt-swiss-ratchet-ln-greenlights-diy-upgrade-kit-converts-pawl-hubs-to-ratchet-engagement/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">LN MTB kits</a> debuted earlier this year, now road, gravel &amp; cyclocross riders with DT pawl hubs can step up to Star Ratchet internals with the straightforward conversion kits.</p><p>Plus, due to popular demand, DT Swiss has added a complete MTB kit option with a 36T Ratchet for faster off-road engagement.</p><h2>DT Swiss Ratchet LN Road hub upgrades</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/RfFBlLnW6sg?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>The same rationale from mountain biking transitions to drop bars here. Upgrade from 3-pawls to a DT’s signature Star Ratchet for faster hub engagement (and the ability to upgrade further), more secure power transfer, and much-improved durability.</p><p>Now, most old 350/370 series road hubs and 1600/1800 series complete road wheels can get upgraded to 240-level performance. Bring OEM spec wheels up to aftermarket performance levels.</p><h3>What’s different for the road?</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4.jpg\" alt=\"shimano 12 speed road group setup and installation tips\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/11174557/shimano-ultregra-12-speed-R8100-derailleur-chain-setup-4-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Well, not much really. A lot of cyclists with older DT road hubs &amp; wheels could have already upgraded using the MTB kits. But now, 18T Ratchet LN Road upgrade kits include the correct modern road freehub body standards: Shimano Road HG 11-speed (<em>which semi-confusingly, but thankfully works with their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-dura-ace-and-ultegra-deliver-fastest-shifting-ever-with-wireless-12-speed-groups/\">new 12-speed groups</a></em>) and the longer SRAM XD-R drivers for <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=SRAM+eTap+AXS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">12-speed AXS</a> drivetrains.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR.jpg\" alt=\"DT Swiss Ratchet LN Upgrade Kit Road, XDR exploded\" width=\"1200\" height=\"720\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17074930/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-Upgrade-Kit-Road_star-ratchet-hub-conversion_XDR-768x461.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The Ratchet LN Upgrade Kit Road includes all the parts (<em>but not the tools</em>) needed for the hub conversion: the new Threaded Ratchet Ring, a pair of 18T ratchets, springs, shim ring, spacer, grease, and the freehub body of your choice. The Shimano Road 11 kit sells for $92 / 70€, and the SRAM XD-R kit sells for $105 / 80€ – both available now.</p><h3>New 36T Ratchet LN MTB upgrade kits</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents.jpg\" alt=\"DT Swiss Ratchet LN hub upgrade kit, from 3-pawls to Star Ratchet,&nbsp;kit contents\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-696x418.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-1068x641.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-1920x1152.jpg 1920w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040944/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_contents-700x420.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>Just like the road, those original <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dt-swiss-ratchet-ln-greenlights-diy-upgrade-kit-converts-pawl-hubs-to-ratchet-engagement/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ratchet LN MTB</a> upgrade kits launched back in April included 18T ratchets for 20° engagement. But many mountain bikes want quicker engagement than that. So on top of the $92-105 / 70-80€&nbsp; for the LN kit, DIYers could easily spend just as much extra if they wanted more teeth. DT heard you, and is making it simple.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded.jpg\" alt=\"DT Swiss Ratchet LN hub upgrade kit, from 3-pawls to Star Ratchet, exploded\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-297x165.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-800x444.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-120x67.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-768x427.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-1536x853.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-696x387.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-1068x593.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/12040902/DT-Swiss-Ratchet-LN-hub-upgrade-kit_from-3-pawls-to-Star-Ratchet_exploded-756x420.jpg 756w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>Now, Ratchet LN MTB kits are also available with 36T ratchet rings from the start, for $52/40€ extra.</p><p>Standard alloy Shimano freehub 36T LN kits are still the cheapest upgrade at $144 / 110€, then alloy XD or MicroSpline for $157 / 120€. Heavy-duty stainless steel freehub bodies are also available with 36T LN kits for $26 / 20€ extra. All are available now through multiple DT Swiss retailer &amp; service center channels.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.dtswiss.com/en/wheels/wheels-technology/ratchet-ln-technology\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>DTSwiss.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8a45f9f22c2d69bfb254f607a286de4d6eb7b8462103e356f5e9a40555b826a7","category":"Cycling"}